.TH QIFTOP\-AGENT.CONF 5 "2026-06-10" "qiftop 0.2.2" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
qiftop\-agent.conf \- configuration file for qiftop\-agent
.SH SYNOPSIS
.I /etc/qiftop/agent.conf
.SH DESCRIPTION
Configuration for
.BR qiftop\-agent (8),
read once at startup. The format is INI as parsed by Qt's
.B QSettings(IniFormat)
\(em
.BI [ section ]
headers followed by
.IB key = value
lines;
.RB ` # '
begins a comment.
.PP
The file is optional: a missing file yields built\-in defaults. Unknown
keys are ignored (forward\-compatible). Numeric values are bounded by the
loader so typos do not produce degenerate cadences: rejected values warn and
fall back to the built\-in default, while documented clamps are noted below. On Debian/RPM installs the file is a
.B conffile
so local edits survive package upgrades. Override the path with
.BR "qiftop\-agent \-\-config " \fIpath\fR.
.SH "SECTION [poll]"
.TP
.BI base_interval_ms= N
Baseline poll cadence in milliseconds when clients are active. Default
.BR 1000 .
Accepted range [\fBmin_interval_ms\fR, 3600000]; invalid values fall back to
the default.
.TP
.BI min_interval_ms= N
Absolute floor for client cadence hints \(em the fastest the agent will
ever poll, regardless of how aggressive a hint is. Default
.BR 100 .
Accepted range [10, 3600000]. This is the DoS guard against a client
pinning the netlink subsystem.
.SH "SECTION [idle]"
.TP
.BI timeout_secs= N
Seconds with no incoming method call after which polling is paused
entirely (near\-zero CPU; the next call wakes it). Default
.BR 60 .
Accepted range [0, 86400] seconds;
.B 0
disables the idle pause.
.TP
.BI hint_ttl_secs= N
How long a client cadence hint (\fBSetDesiredIntervalMs\fR) stays in
effect after the client's last call. Clients should re\-assert at roughly
half this value. Default
.BR 10 .
Positive values up to 86400 seconds are accepted; 0 or negative values fall
back to the default, and larger values clamp to 86400. Sub-second values are
not expressible in the INI. Disconnected clients' hints expire silently.
.TP
.BI schedule= "w1:i1,w2:i2,w3:0"
Adaptive slow\-down schedule: three
.IB window_secs : interval_ms
pairs. Window values are seconds in the range [0, 86400]; interval values are
milliseconds in [\fBmin_interval_ms\fR, 3600000]. Read left to right:
elapsed < \fIw1\fR uses
.BR base_interval_ms ;
\fIw1\fR..\fIw2\fR uses \fIi1\fR; \fIw2\fR..\fIw3\fR uses \fIi2\fR; beyond
\fIw3\fR polling pauses. Default
.BR 30:2000,45:5000,60:0 .
The third interval is the "paused" sentinel and is ignored; \fIw3\fR
should match
.BR timeout_secs .
.SH "SECTION [process_details]"
Controls who may read the
.B privileged
per\-process fields \(em
.IR exe ", " cwd " and the full " "command line" " \(em"
returned by the
.B Connections.GetProcessDetails(pid)
D\-Bus method. The low\-sensitivity bulk fields
.RB ( pid ", " uid ", " comm ", " "start time" )
are
.B always
returned to any authorised (netdev\-group) caller and are unaffected by
this section.
.PP
The root agent can read
.IR /proc/<pid>/exe " and " /proc/<pid>/cwd
for processes owned by other users (it holds
.BR CAP_SYS_PTRACE / CAP_DAC_READ_SEARCH
for attribution), and
.I /proc/<pid>/cmdline
can carry secrets passed on the command line; this key bounds how widely
the agent re\-discloses them.
.TP
.BI disclosure= mode
.RS
.TP
.B owner
Root or the process's own owner only. (default)
.TP
.B permissive
Any authorised (netdev) caller \(em every netdev member sees every
process's
.IR exe / cwd / cmdline .
Restores the pre\-0.2.1 behaviour.
.TP
.B restricted
Root, the process owner,
.B or
a caller named in
.B allow_users
/ a member of a group in
.B allow_groups
(e.g.
.BR wheel ).
Grants cross\-user visibility to a small set of administrators without
opening it to the whole netdev group.
.RE
The canonical values are
.BR owner ,
.BR permissive
and
.BR restricted ;
compatibility aliases
.BR all
(for permissive) and
.BR users
(for restricted) are also accepted. An unrecognised value warns and falls
back to
.BR owner .
.TP
.BI allow_users= "name[,name...]"
Login names granted cross\-UID detail access in
.B restricted
mode. Comma\- or whitespace\-separated. Default empty.
.TP
.BI allow_groups= "group[,group...]"
Group names granted cross\-UID detail access in
.B restricted
mode; matches primary
.B or
supplementary membership. Comma\- or whitespace\-separated. Default empty.
.PP
With
.B restricted
and both lists empty, behaviour is identical to
.BR owner .
.SH EXAMPLES
A laptop that wants snappier updates and lets the
.B wheel
admins inspect any process:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
[poll]
base_interval_ms=500

[idle]
timeout_secs=30
schedule=15:1000,25:3000,30:0

[process_details]
disclosure=restricted
allow_groups=wheel
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR qiftop\-agent (8),
.BR qiftop (1),
.BR nqiftop (1)
.SH HOMEPAGE
https://github.com/TheCleaners/qiftop
